parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
or hesitates when shifting; the vehicle jerks or lunges forward; the transmission makes a grinding or clunking noise; the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; the clutch pedal sticks to the floor; the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position; the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the reverse gear can cause the vehicle to roll away or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away or moves unexpectedly when in reverse gear; the vehicle fails to engage into reverse gear; the transmission makes a grinding or clunking noise when shifting into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Park Pawl Rod Guide Cup Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the park pawl rod guide cup can cause the vehicle to roll away or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away or moves unexpectedly when in park; the parking brake does not engage properly; the transmission makes a grinding or clunking noise when shifting into park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel cluster can cause the driver to lose access to critical information, such as speed, fuel level, and warning lights, which can lead to accidents or other safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument panel cluster goes blank
or becomes unresponsive; the driver is unable to access critical information

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rearview camera can cause the driver to lose visibility while reversing, which can lead to accidents or other safety risks.
symptoms: The rearview camera display goes blank or displays incorrect information; the driver is unable to see behind the vehicle while reversing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of doors and windows can cause the driver or passengers to become trapped or injured, which can lead to accidents or other safety risks.
symptoms: The doors or windows become stuck or difficult to operate; the doors or windows open or close unexpectedly while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power or become inoperable, which can lead to accidents or other safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or becomes inoperable; the electrical system malfunctions
causing unexpected shutdowns or loss of critical systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the battery terminals can cause the vehicle to lose power or become inoperable, which can lead to accidents or other safety risks.
symptoms: causing electrical connections to fail; the vehicle loses power or becomes inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Coolant Leaks and Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall, overheat, or catch on fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The design flaw in the coolant channels can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to engine failure.
The engine knocking or ticking noise can be a sign of engine damage, leading to premature engine failure, misfires, and loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds.
The failure of the door latch can cause the door to open or unlatch while driving, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The door unlatches or opens while driving
the door ajar warning light and chime activate
wind rushes in around the closed window
the door opens randomly while driving
the door opens when going over bumps or railroad tracks.
